org.nerd4j.csv.reader.binding

Interface CSVToModelBinder<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - type of the data model representing the CSV record.

    public interface CSVToModelBinder<M>
    Represents an object able to build and fill a data model using the fields of a related CSV record.
    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void fill(int column, Object value)
      Fills the model with the given value related to the given column.
      M getModel()
      Returns the internal model instance.
      void initModel()
      Creates a new empty model to be filled with the given data by the method fill(int,Object).

    • Method Detail

      • initModel

        void initModel()
               throws CSVToModelBindingException
        Creates a new empty model to be filled with the given data by the method fill(int,Object).

        If a model already exists will be overridden with a new empty instance.

        Throws:
        CSVToModelBindingException - if the initialization of the model fails.

      • fill

        void fill(int column,
        Object value)
          throws CSVToModelBindingException
        Fills the model with the given value related to the given column.
        Parameters:
        column - related column.
        value - value to fill with.
        Throws:
        CSVToModelBindingException - if the operation fails for some reason.

      • getModel

        M getModel()
        Returns the internal model instance.

        If the model has never been initializad returns null.

        Returns:
        the internal model instance.
